This is a tier 4 staged surf map with 6 stages. Its a fairly active map with lots of big jumps. Each stage is challenging and satisfying to complete. Each stage is about 20 - 30 seconds long, so a full run should be about 2 and a half to 3 minutes for a no-fail. The visual style is minimalistic and was inspired by surf_polygon. The textures are custom made by me to achieve a flat shaded minimal look. The surf was also inspired by polygon along with other surfs like stonework. 

There are timer triggers at the start of each stage and at the end; the name are: stage1_start, stage2_start, stage3_start, stage4_start, stage5_start, stage6_start, and mapend.

Here is a video showcasing the map: 
<iframe width="560" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/ZxUK5z7hI-Y" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

I would like to extend a huge thank you to the ksf community and specifically: Juxtapo, Sacred, Krazy, mbsurfer, streebree, and everyone who helped me shape this map. I had a really fun time making and surfing this map, and I hope that everyone who surfs it also enjoys it. Thank you!

Give the map a shot and tell me what you think.

this map has been in production since early February 08.
I have had a total of 4 beta tests to get rid of all bugs, and im positive there all gone.
The name in the pictures is _B4 i know but i have changed the .bsp's name to just surf_annoyance.

About the map:
there is a 5 min. timer, that after 5 min choses one of 4 jails randomly for all people to play.
after beating the map the timer is stopped and the person who beat the map can choose one of 3 jails (2 of witch are available from no one beating the map).
there are a total of 8 surf areas:
1.1, 1.2, 1.3, 2.1, 2.2, 2.3, 3.1, 3.2
the different first # signifies a different texture set.

The jails:

Knife Fight- 
two people (one from each team) go into the knife fight area, and get a knife.
after one person dies, that persons, teams door opens, letting someone else challenge the winner of the previous fight.
this jail can only be gotten to by no one beating the map.

Dodge Jail-
bars come along the floor, increasing in number, for the players to dodge.
if a player fails to dodge or avoid a bar then they are killed.
this jail can only be gotten to by no one beating the map.

Para vs knife-
everyone spawns and gets a knife.
there is a para with allot of ammo in the middle of the room.
this jail can be gotten to both ways (someone beating the map, or no one)  
if chosen by someone who beat the map, they spawn on the para.

Gun Game-
a gun game style jail, two sides (T and CT).
players get better weapons depending on where they were in the map.
there is a hole in the middle of this jail, don't fall in you will die
this jail can be gotten to both ways (someone beating the map, or no one)  
if chosen by someone who beat the map, they get what people in the last level would get.

Kill-
can only be gotten to by someone beating the map.
the winner controls a small vehicle, and smashes into people with it, killing them.

this is a skill surf map, with areas ranging from easy to expert.
this map has been beaten in the beta tests so don't think its impossible.

i have spent a lot of time on this map, i am vary proud of it.

i hope you enjoy my map.

Surf_amplitude_apex -- (#3 of the amplitude series)
**1 Year anniversary for the series**
Map created by Buck Nasty
Jail created by FAJ
------------------------------

This is a skill surf with 3 stages. (It is meant to be difficult!)

- Both teams spawn together without any weapons (no pistols or knives).

- The screenshots shown are NOT the best. I tried to get the overview of each level but they came out a bit sloppy.

How the jail works:
- The jail timers start counting once a player has beaten the first stage.
- After it the first stage has been beaten, the jail is active and the players that spawn in it are released every 20 seconds.
- After 9 releases (3 mins) it will count 20 seconds before the auto-kill engages.
- Also, after 3 mins, jump rope is disabled (The timer for this starts at round start).

Upon entering the jail you receive...
- Stage 1: Nothing
- Stage 2: A grenade
- Stage 3: Nothing, but your level of jail has grenade spawners

I'd rather not ask for constructive criticism cause I honestly don't care, this map is the way Faj & I like it. Although, compliments are welcome.

-- Buck Nasty

This map is quite popular on the BB 24/7 Surf server. I am an admin there, but most of the time I find myself mapping the hours away. This is my first surf map, my other map is fun_hobbes. I am working on a new map, surf_sniper, which includes HDR lighting.

A comment I receive a lot about this map is how intuitive the jail system works! If anyone has ever played this map, it's very annoying trying to have to jump over the hills and valleys, constantly under fire by sniper bullets and AUGs. It's easy to just turn around and shoot into the sniper den, but its harder to get the jailtop campers! There are a few secrets scattered around the jail area, as well.

I really wanted to work with surf maps after the success of completing fun_hobbes. Hopefully this accounts for it. I will release fun_hobbes and my most recent creation, surf_intheair, very soon. Hopefully I'll tag a few more screenshots in. Thank you so much for reviewing this and I hope you will put it on your server!
~ hobbes312

I chose to do this cause I like to mix it up and make things new and interesting. Regular surfing to me is bland and boring, and I like the challenge of something different.
